OL,3,CGlass marbles used to invent WW2's
OL,4,C'bouncing bomb' sell for #15k
OL,6,FTwo glass marbles used by an aviation
OL,7,Fengineer to invent World War Two's
OL,8,Ffamous 'bouncing bomb' have sold for
OL,9,Fmore than #15,000 at auction.
OL,11,FSir Barnes Wallis' marbles sold for
OL,12,F#15,200 to a private collector in the
OL,13,FUK when they went under the hammer at
OL,14,FAuctioneum, in Bristol, on Monday 16
OL,15,FSeptember.
OL,17,FMr Wallis used the marbles while
OL,18,Fworking on plans for a bomb that could
OL,19,Fskip across water, experimenting with
OL,20,Fbouncing them across an old tin bath
OL,21,Fin his back garden.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/6
