OL,6,FHe added: "The effect that these
OL,7,Fmarbles had on the war effort, on
OL,8,Fmorale for the British people, it's
OL,9,Famazing. They are so significant.
OL,11,F"For all intensive purposes these are
OL,12,Fjust two marbles, two 1930s childhood
OL,13,Fglass marbles, but their contribution
OL,14,Fto our combined history is
OL,15,Fimmesurable."
OL,17,FThe marbles were auctioned alongside a
OL,18,Fpair of Sir Barnes Wallis' binoculars,
OL,19,Fwhich he used to watch his bomb being
OL,20,Ftested in Reculver, Kent.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
